The Economics of Open Content Symposium: The Wealth of Networks
Yochai Benkler, Yale Law School

Yale University Law School Professor Yochai Benkler explores the new economies and the powerful transformative potential of decentralized social production.

The Wealth of Networks: How Social Production Transforms Markets and Freedom
Yochai Benkler, Yale Law School

On January 23-24, 2006, Intelligent Televison hosts the Economics of Open Content symposium at MIT to bring together representatives from media industries, cultural and educational institutions, and legal and business minds to discuss how to make open content happen better and faster.

